<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Resources - FIRST Start</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/main.css?v=21">
</head>
<body>
  <header></header>

  <main>
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/" class="btn btn-secondary back-button">&larr; Back Home</a>

      <h1>Resources</h1>

      <p class="subtitle">
        Choose FTC, FRC, or FLL Challenge to see resources that match the program you are building for.
      </p>

      <section class="program-choice resources-program-choice" aria-labelledby="resourcesProgramTitle">
        <h2 id="resourcesProgramTitle">Choose Your Program</h2>
        <div class="program-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="FIRST program resources">
          <input type="radio" name="resources-program" id="resources-program-ftc" checked>
          <label for="resources-program-ftc">FTC</label>

          <input type="radio" name="resources-program" id="resources-program-frc">
          <label for="resources-program-frc">FRC</label>

          <input type="radio" name="resources-program" id="resources-program-fll">
          <label for="resources-program-fll">FLL Challenge</label>
        </div>

        <div class="program-panel program-panel-ftc">
          <div class="resources-grid">
            <div class="resource-card">
              <div class="card-icon">FTC</div>
              <h2>Software</h2>
              <p>Learn how to write robot code, configure the controller app, and understand the FTC SDK workflow.</p>
              <ul class="resource-links">
                <li>
                  <a href="/sdk">FTC SDK Documentation</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Official Java robot libraries, setup steps, and the core classes used in FTC coding.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/programming">Basic FTC Robot Programming</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Start here if you are new to OpModes, drivetrain control, and tele-op basics.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/advanced-programming">Advanced FTC Robot Programming</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Covers better architecture, autonomous routines, and more advanced coding patterns.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/controller-setup">Robot Controller Setup</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Shows how to connect phones, pair devices, and get the control system ready to test.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="resource-card">
              <div class="card-icon">Build</div>
              <h2>Mechanical</h2>
              <p>Plan a robot that is sturdy, easy to repair, and realistic for your team to build and maintain.</p>
              <ul class="resource-links">
                <li>
                  <a href="/drivetrain">Drivetrain Design</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Compare drive styles, wheel choices, gearing, and layout ideas for a dependable base.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/mechanical-parts">Mechanical Parts Guide</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">A practical overview of fasteners, structure pieces, motion parts, and common hardware.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/assembly">Assembly Tutorials</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Step-by-step build help for putting together parts cleanly and keeping the robot serviceable.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/motor-selection">Motor Selection</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Helps you choose the right motors and understand power, speed, and torque tradeoffs.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="resource-card">
              <div class="card-icon">Team</div>
              <h2>Non-Technical</h2>
              <p>Use these guides to organize your team, explain your goals, and build support from families and sponsors.</p>
              <ul class="resource-links">
                <li>
                  <a href="/funding">Team Funding Guide</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Budget planning, sponsor outreach, and ways to explain where the money will go.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/sponsorship">Sponsorship Templates</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Email and letter templates that help you ask businesses and organizations for support.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/outreach">Outreach Ideas</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Ways to recruit students, show off the team, and share FIRST with your community.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/team-org">Team Organization</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Learn how to set roles, track tasks, and keep meetings productive throughout the season.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="program-panel program-panel-frc">
          <div class="resources-grid">
            <div class="resource-card">
              <div class="card-icon">FRC</div>
              <h2>Team Setup</h2>
              <p>Build the structure, people, and budget a larger robotics team needs before the season gets busy.</p>
              <ul class="resource-links">
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-team-setup">FRC Program Overview</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">FRC basics, team structure, and official overview links in one local guide.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-team-setup">Team Management Resources</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Student roles, mentor roles, meeting expectations, and team operations.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-team-setup">Cost and Registration</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">First-year budgeting, registration planning, and official cost links.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-team-setup">Find Teams and Events</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">How to use nearby teams and events to learn before competing.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="resource-card">
              <div class="card-icon">Build</div>
              <h2>Robot Build Basics</h2>
              <p>Plan a large robot that is safe, serviceable, and realistic for your team to finish and practice with.</p>
              <ul class="resource-links">
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-robot-build">WPILib Documentation</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Programming setup, controls, simulation, and official WPILib links inside.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-robot-build">Zero to Robot</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Setup path for laptops, roboRIO, radio hardware, wiring, and deployment.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-robot-build">FRC Technical Resources</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Robot control, inspection, and build support guidance for new teams.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-robot-build">Kit and Season Materials</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">How to use kit and kickoff details when planning robot build scope.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="resource-card">
              <div class="card-icon">Game</div>
              <h2>Season and Events</h2>
              <p>Use these resources to prepare for kickoff, inspection, judging, pit work, matches, and event logistics.</p>
              <ul class="resource-links">
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-season-events">FRC Season Materials</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Manuals, updates, deadlines, and how to turn them into a season plan.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-season-events">Safety Manual</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Shop, pit, battery, tool, lifting, and event safety expectations.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-season-events">Awards and Submissions</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">How to prepare students for impact, technical, and interview-based awards.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/frc-season-events">Teams and Events Search</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">How event listings help with travel, scouting, practice, and scheduling.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="program-panel program-panel-fll">
          <div class="resources-grid">
            <div class="resource-card">
              <div class="card-icon">FLL</div>
              <h2>Team Meetings</h2>
              <p>Organize a small team, steady meeting rhythm, and coaching structure that lets students own the work.</p>
              <ul class="resource-links">
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-team-meetings">How to Get Started</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Team setup, coach responsibilities, registration, and partner connection guidance.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-team-meetings">FIRST LEGO League Site</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Program structure, divisions, season theme, and family explanation help.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-team-meetings">Cost and Registration</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Registration, Challenge Set, robot materials, supplies, and event budget notes.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-team-meetings">Youth Protection</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Adult supervision, student safety, communication, and meeting expectations.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="resource-card">
              <div class="card-icon">Robot</div>
              <h2>Robot Game and Coding</h2>
              <p>Build a reliable LEGO robot, test one mission at a time, and keep programs simple enough for students to explain.</p>
              <ul class="resource-links">
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-robot-game">Robot Game Rulebook</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Mission scoring, match flow, challenge updates, and field setup guidance.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-robot-game">SPIKE Prime Lessons</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Beginner-friendly robot building, coding, sensors, and testing lessons.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-robot-game">SPIKE App</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Robot coding, motor control, sensors, mission routines, and debugging basics.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-robot-game">Challenge Resources</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Mission testing, attachments, robot design judging, and season resources.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="resource-card">
              <div class="card-icon">Project</div>
              <h2>Innovation Project and Event Prep</h2>
              <p>Prepare for the parts of FLL beyond robot matches: project research, Core Values, robot design, and judging.</p>
              <ul class="resource-links">
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-project-event">Team Meeting Guide</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Meeting pacing for project work, robot design, Core Values, and events.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-project-event">Engineering Notebook</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Track ideas, testing, robot changes, project research, and team decisions.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-project-event">Judging Resources</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Prepare students to explain project, robot design, teamwork, and iteration.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/resources/fll-project-event">Teams and Events Search</a>
                  <span class="resource-link-note">Find events, nearby teams, and examples of competition day organization.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <script src="/assets/js/main.js?v=37"></script>
</body>
</html>
